Windows Virtual Machines

These are new virtual machine which will be launched for a specific task. They will not be always on like the previous virtual machines. It is up to you to shut down the machine when you are no longer using it, to free up resources for other users. We will likely create a number of machine of different sizes to different tasks.

If you have a large MaxQuant job to run, then you can spawn a large machine with lots of CPUs and RAM. If you have a small job to run the use a smaller machine, adequate to the task at hand.

srvwinbbl

Log into Virtual Machine using a Remote Desktop application with the following settings.

It looks like each of us will get our own user access to these virtual machines, unlike the previous ones, where everyone used one login.

Im not sure how admin access on these machines works yet, let me know if you run into any issues and what software needs to be installed. Id like to build documentation around installation and operation of software, so we know what we have in operation.

Installation

Supported operation system versions (64 bit is required) are Windows Vista, 7, 8, 10, Server 2008, 2012.

Install .NET Framework 4.7.3 or higher

The following were installed at: C:Files

  • NET SDK 5.0.201
  • NET Runtime 5.0.4
  • ASP.NET Core Runtime 5.0.4
  • NET Windows Desktop Runtime 5.0.4
